op align=left class=m><span class=title> NToV rotation ??</span><hr size=1> There are currently 4 guilds actively doing NToV (DG,KX,RoD,Aff) and a few more that probably will be before too long.<br><br>I think there should be at least some sort of understanding amongst Emarr guilds when it comes to NToV to avoid future arguements.<br><br>Just off the top of my head I would say there are 3 ways to go with NToV.<br><br>1) First come, first serve.  <br><br>Whoever gets a raid force set up and pulling NToV mobs first wins.  It would be considered bad form to CoH ahead of a guild that is already fighting their way in.<br><br>2) Rotation - can be done a couple ways.  <br><br>One way would be one calendar week all spawns go to one guild.  You get into the rotation by killing Roy before the current guild in the rotation.  <br><br>Another way would be to run it like Trak/VS.  To get into rotation you have to get Roy before the current guild in the rotation.  Give the current guild in the rotation up to 2 days after Roy kill to finish clearing.  After that the mobs become FFA.<br><br>3) Modified first come, first serve.  <br><br>First guild to kill Roy gets rights to all NToV mobs past Roy for a certain period of time (like 2 days).  After that it would be FFA until next Roy pop.<br><br><br>I'm just trying to find out which of the 3 options most seem to think is the way to go.  Try to limit the discussion to either one of the above choices, or another suggestion for a better way to do it.  <br><br>Let's not bring up old stuff here.  Let's just come up with some sort of a solution to avoid any problems in the future. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ughie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 532<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/23/02 10:25:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboa